news.title: Help desk for online registration of vacant Prayagraj development body's flats
news.para: These flats cater to various categories, including EWS, LIG, 1BHK, 2BHK, and 3BHK, and will be allocated through a lottery system, providing a fair opportunity to prospective buyers.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body collects ₹60 crore property tax during two-month rebate period
news.para: The final figures might increase slightly, but this collection marks the highest amount ever received during a two-month rebate period.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body set to proceed after getting estate office’s nod on freehold
news.para: Meanwhile, the Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) informed the MC that they do not engage in activities involving the disposal of chunks of land.

news.title: Over 40 Noida societies lack pollution board nod to operate STPs
news.para: It permits industries, commercial establishments, and group housing societies to operate their facilities while ensuring that their emissions, effluents, and waste management systems comply with environmental standards.

news.title: Telangana RERA to establish enforcement wing to ensure swift compliance
news.para: TGRERA has been given more teeth with district collectors now empowered to invoke the Revenue Recovery Act (RRA) and exercise certain civil court powers for enforcement. This marks a decisive shift from passive regulation to active enforcement, sources said.

news.title: Will demolish buildings causing floods: Karnataka deputy CM
news.para: Shivamkumar, who inspected flood-prone areas in Yelahanka zone and Manyata Tech Park, said, "Whether it is your building or mine, it has to go if it is hindering the free flow of rainwater."

news.title: Mussoorie Dehradun development body to identify land bank for residential projects
news.para: This move was prompted by the rising population density and the success of previous initiatives such as the ISBT and Aamwala Tarla residential schemes.

news.title: Delhi government mandates anti-smog guns for all high-rise buildings
news.para: Delhi Environment Minister Manjinder Singh Sirsa said the number of anti-smog guns required will depend on the building's built-up area.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body issues notices to 82 dangerous buildings after pre-monsoon survey
news.para: Civic officials said there was a significant drop in the number of such structures compared to the last two years. They attributed the decline to building owners who either undertook repairs or opted for demolition.

news.title: Indore development body to sell flats, plots & shops to boost revenue, targets ₹261 crore
news.para: A decision to sell 600 flats, 40 shops, and 24 plots was made during an IDA board meeting, chaired by the Divisional Commissioner Deepak Singh, Collector Asheesh Singh, IMC Commissioner Shivam Verma, and IDA CEO RP Ahirwar among other officials on Friday.

news.title: Tata Digital leases 59,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai’s Lower Parel
news.para: The company will be paying monthly rentals of Rs 1.05 crore and common area maintenance (CAM) charges of Rs 12.32 lakh, translating to a blended outgo of around Rs 1.18 crore per month.

news.title: Urban residents across Andhra Pradesh fret over proposed increase in property tax
news.para: Civic and taxpayers associations were hearing to take up protest against the proposed hike. Associations alleged that the cumulative burden, expected to touch 784 crore statewide, has become a point of contention among citizens and civic groups alike.

news.title: Transit oriented development in Meerut to unlock real estate on Namo Bharat corridor
news.para: Meerut Development Authority (MEDA) has earmarked about 3,273 hectares for the TOD, out of which 2,442 hectares have been delineated into seven TOD zones and two special development area (SDA) zones around the Namo Bharat and Meerut Metro corridors.

news.title: Lucknow development body to develop Udyog Nagar, Naimish Nagar
news.para: Singh said that Udyog Nagar will be developed over 5,610 acres in Sadar and Sarojininagar tehsils. Land was identified in villages, including Bhaliya, Adampur Indwara, Behru, Jaliamau, Madarpur and Ibrahimganj.

news.title: Centre set to push amendments to DDA, to give fillip to land pooling policy
news.para: The Centre is planning to push amendments to the Delhi Development Act which will make land pooling mandatory for all residents if a certain percentage -- 70% -- of owners of land in an area agree to pool land.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to launch three-month drive to regularise or raze unauthorised constructions
news.para: During a review of the housing development authorities, it was found that out of the 2.50 lakh complaints pertaining to unauthorised and illegal construction activity forwarded to authorities during the 2024-25 financial year, only 3,507 have been disposed of, while the remaining ones remain pending.

news.title: Lucknow: Lottery for Anant Nagar Scheme plots on June 10
news.para: District magistrate Vishakh G recently inspected the site and reviewed development progress. He directed the officials to widen the connecting road between the scheme and UPSIDA as well as Kisan Path.

news.title: Prayagraj development body offers 764 flats for sale
news.para: The flats cater to various categories, including EWS, LIG, 1BHK, 2BHK, and 3BHK, and will be allocated through a lottery system, providing a fair opportunity to prospective buyers.

news.title: Developers get Gujarat RERA notices for pre-registration bookings
news.para: Sources said that GujRERA is going to start a mega campaign against this practice across the state. The authority also announced new rules for the marketing of projects, which will come into effect from June 15.
